body:
For functions with many arguments it would be nice if we could pass them by name.  This greatly enhances code readability.

```
% iverilog -g2012 argbynamebug.sv
argbynamebug.sv:15: syntax error
argbynamebug.sv:15: error: malformed statement
```

```
module argbynamebug;

function automatic logic [3:0] sum(logic [3:0] a, logic [3:0] b);
begin
  return a + b;
end
endfunction

initial begin
  logic [3:0] my_a, my_b, my_y;

  my_a = 4'd5;
  my_b = 4'd3;

  my_y = sum(.a(my_a), .b(my_b)); // arguments by name: syntax error
  //my_y = sum(my_a, my_b);      // positional OK

  $display("%d", my_y);
  $finish();
end

endmodule
```

